# Repo Context — full reference (Cursor pointer)

**Canonical document:** **`REPO_CONTEXT_REFERENCE.md`** in this **package root** (same directory as `AGENTS.md`). It contains every MCP tool, workflow, file-size rules, semantic annotation workflow, and limitations. Use **Read** on that path when you need the long form.

This rule stays tiny on purpose: users may ship repo-context **without** `.cursor/`. Do not rely on a copy of the full text living only under `.cursor/rules/`.

**Mini cheat sheet:** map → `get_domain_or_focus_context` / `get_domain_modules_slice`; detail → `get_context_detail` (no body first); then `includeBody` / `grepBody` / Read by `lineRange`. Types → `get_dependency_impact`. Env vars → `get_env_vars_usage`. HTTP down → `npm run mcp:http` or `npm run ui` (port **3334**).
